## Component Details

### ModalContainer.vue

The ModalContainer component provides a centered overlay for support pages.

**Properties:**

-   `isOpen` (Boolean): Whether the modal is currently displayed
-   `title` (String): The title to display in the header
-   `size` (String): Size variant ("small", "medium", "large", "fullscreen")
-   `showCloseButton` (Boolean): Whether to show the close button

**Events:**

-   `@close`: Emitted when the close button is clicked or backdrop is clicked
-   `@animationComplete`: Emitted when open/close animations complete

**Implementation Notes:**

-   Semi-transparent backdrop that dims the main application
-   Smooth open/close animations
-   Responsive sizing based on content and screen size
-   Focus trap for accessibility
-   Scrollable content area for longer pages

### DrawerPanel.vue

The DrawerPanel component provides a sliding panel from the edge of the screen.

**Properties:**

-   `isOpen` (Boolean): Whether the drawer is currently displayed
-   `title` (String): The title to display in the header
-   `position` (String): Which edge to slide from ("left", "right", "bottom")
-   `width` (String): Width of the drawer (for left/right positions)
-   `height` (String): Height of the drawer (for bottom position)
-   `showCloseButton` (Boolean): Whether to show the close button

**Events:**

-   `@close`: Emitted when the close button is clicked or backdrop is clicked
-   `@animationComplete`: Emitted when open/close animations complete

**Implementation Notes:**

-   Smooth slide animations
-   Semi-transparent backdrop
-   Responsive sizing
-   Touch gestures for closing (swipe)
-   Focus trap for accessibility

## Navigation Integration

The left sidebar navigation continues to provide access to these support pages, but now opens them as overlays instead of navigating to new routes.

**Implementation Notes:**
- Navigation links emit events to open the appropriate modal/drawer
- Current application state is preserved while viewing support pages
- Browser history is not affected by opening/closing these overlays
- Keyboard shortcuts provide quick access to common settings

## Settings View

The Settings View is now displayed as a modal/drawer overlay while maintaining all existing functionality. This allows users to adjust their preferences without losing their context in the main application.

**Key Features:**
- All settings categories (Appearance, Notifications, Privacy, Account Verification) remain accessible
- Changes take effect immediately without requiring page navigation
- The modal can be dismissed to return to the exact previous state
- Settings are organized into logical groups with clear labels

## Profile View

The Profile View is now displayed as a modal/drawer overlay, allowing users to view their profile information without navigating away from their current context.

**Key Features:**
- Profile statistics and information are readily accessible
- Social sharing options for profile content
- Bestie matches displayed with similarity percentages
- Public profile link for sharing with other users



## About View

The About View is now displayed as a modal/drawer overlay, providing information about the application without requiring users to navigate away from their current context.

**Key Features:**
- Application information and version details remain accessible
- Credits and contact information are clearly displayed
- The modal can be dismissed to return to the exact previous state
- Content is organized in a readable, scrollable format

## Terms/Privacy View

The Terms/Privacy View is now displayed as a modal/drawer overlay, allowing users to review legal information without losing their place in the application.

**Key Features:**
- Tabbed interface separates Terms of Service and Privacy Policy
- Legal content is presented in a readable, scrollable format
- Last updated timestamp shows when legal documents were modified
- The modal can be dismissed to return to the exact previous state



## Navigation Integration

The left sidebar navigation continues to provide access to these support pages, but now opens them as overlays instead of navigating to new routes.

**Implementation Notes:**

-   Navigation links emit events to open the appropriate modal/drawer
-   Current application state is preserved while viewing support pages
-   Browser history is not affected by opening/closing these overlays
-   Keyboard shortcuts provide quick access to common settings

# Summary of All Required Changes

Based on my analysis of the feature enhancement plan and the current documentation, here's a summary of the changes required for each document:

**README.md**

-   Add the new feature enhancements to the key enhancements list

**Sidebar Panel**

-   Revise to focus on personal reviews and comments for songs and eras
-   Support one editable review per song/era with edit history
-   Add unlimited sequential blog-like comments
-   Implement tallying of reviews and comments across users
-   Split Review & Notes tab into separate Review and Comments tabs

**Edit Rankings View**

-   Add Quick Ranking feature (3x3 format)
-   Implement mode selection between Quick Rank and Full Rank
-   Add sorting options for songs (by position or personal ranking)
-   Ensure minimum requirements for saving (3 eras with 3 songs each)

**Dashboard View**

-   Add sorting options for eras (by release date or personal ranking)
-   Update era cards to show review and comment tallies
-   Ensure compatibility with the new sidebar functionality

**Support Pages (Settings, Profile, About, Legal)**

-   Convert all support pages to modal/drawer views
-   Ensure these views overlay the main application without navigating away
-   Maintain the same functionality and content within the modal/drawer format

These changes will create a more streamlined user experience with enhanced functionality for reviews, comments, ranking, and navigation. The implementation maintains the core functionality of the application while adding new features that improve usability and engagement.

Would you like me to provide more detailed changes for any specific document or feature?
